#MeetTheTeam
.
Meet Antonella's little cutie pie 🥰
.
Faustino worked as our Director of Hugs from the moment he was born until a year ago, when he turned 3 and decided to change departments. To pursue a career in Fun and Cuteness Management, he now makes sure everyone in the team has a laugh at least once a day.
.
He speaks Spanish, a language of his own we are still trying to learn, and he can count up to 12 in English.

#TranslatorsLife #VidaDeTraductores
.
Put your hand up if you can relate! Anto here, Crisol's CFO and Tourism+Gastronomy translator.
.
Being a freelance translator working from home sometimes means your parenting duties get in the way. You learn to focus despite the noise, you adopt your child's dinosaurs as your new office colleagues, and you adquire flexiblity skills that you never thought you'd have. It can be challenging, but I wouldn't change a bit of it.
.
I'd love to see your parenting+freelancing photos! Leave them in the comments for me, will you?
.
//
.
¡Levanten las manos si se sienten identificados! Soy Anto, directora financiera de Crisol y traductora especializada en gastronomía y turismo.
.
Trabajar como traductora independiente muchas veces implica combinar el trabajo con las tareas parentales. Aprendés a concentrarte a pesar del ruido, adoptás a los dinosaurios de tu hijo como colegas y adquirís una flexibilidad que nunca imaginaste tener. Puede ser un desafío, pero no cambiaría nada.
.
¡Me encantaría ver sus fotos de trabajo y paternidad! ¿Las compartirían con nosotras en los comentarios?
